6. Code Walkthrough
The project is written in a single Python file for simplicity. It is organised into four logical sections:

Function / Section	Purpose
companies (list)	Data store — holds company name, min GPA, and difficulty
calculate_gpa(marks)	Converts raw subject marks to a GPA score on a 10-point scale
selection_probability(gpa, company)	Computes heuristic shortlisting probability for one company
predict_companies(gpa)	Filters eligible companies, scores them, and sorts by probability
main()	Entry point — handles user input/output and orchestrates all functions

The import random statement is present in the original code but unused — it was likely included during iterative development for a planned randomised simulation feature that was later replaced by the deterministic heuristic formula. It has been retained in the final code without causing any functional impact.

