11. Conclusion
A heuristic doesn't need training data to be useful — it needs to be thought through. This project shows that a small, self-contained tool can still produce output worth trusting, as long as the formula behind it has a clear rationale.
The bigger lesson was about sequencing. The formula, the dataset, the ranking order — none of it came from adding features and seeing what worked. It came from thinking about how placement decisions actually get made, then building toward that. The code was the last step, not the first.
